    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Those who follow the art or practice of foreseeing future events or obtaining secret knowledge through divine sources, omens, or oracles; it is based on the belief that revelations are offered to humans in extrarational forms of knowledge.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Aquellos que practican el arte de predecir eventos del futuro o para obtener conocimientos secretos de las fuentes divinas, malos augurios, oráculos; basado en la creencia de que las revelaciones son ofrecidas al humano en extraracionales formas de conocimiento.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zij die zich bezighouden met de kunst of de praktijk van het voorspellen van toekomstige gebeurtenissen of het verkrijgen van geheime kennis via goddelijke bronnen, voortekens of orakels; gebaseerd op het geloof dat openbaringen aan mensen worden gedaan in vormen van kennis die zich aan de ratio onttrekken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>可預見未來之事或透過神啟、預兆或神諭等方式獲得神祕知識者；此係根據一種想法，相信人可藉由超理性的知識形式獲得天啟。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cequin tlen quiyehyecoa quipannextizceh ce tlamantli tlen panoz teipan zo para quimatizceh ce ixtlamatiliztli ica totiotzitzin, tetetzahuianih, tlatemoliztli, motechtia ipan tlaneltoquilli tlen macehualmeh ipan ehelihuiliz ixtlamatiliztli.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
